Interface DatasetTransformContext

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable, TransformContext

    @NotThreadSafe
 @Immutable
public interface DatasetTransformContext
extends TransformContext, Serializable
    Given to a DatasetTransform when it is executed. Provides context information to assist in the execution.

      • getDatasets

        @Nonnull
scala.collection.immutable.Map<String,org.apache.spark.sql.Dataset> getDatasets()
        Get a map of parameter names (of type Parameter.INPUT_DATA_COLLECTION) to DataFrames.

        Note that if a user has assigned multiple input datasets in the UI to an input dataset parameter, the SDK will union those datasets together before returning them in this method.

        Returns:
        a mapping of input dataset parameter names to DataFrames
